Preppin for this NYE show got me reliving my high school years as a Hendrix fanatic. Also I’m once again completely blown away by what Jimi was able to achieve by age of 27. An incredible catalog of music not to mention he completely changed the way we think about the electric guitar. On top of ALL of that he played solos that were SO tasteful and lyrical that we sing them like they are PART of the song. Not many guitarists with that much technical ability choose to play so simple and lyrical. 😁 Denver-> come see us New Year’s Eve at @knew_conscious ⚡️ @rossmfjames @alexkoford_music #JimisDead #windcriesmary

I have always felt that the end of an album has to feel a certain way. There’s a certain nostalgia or longing that I usually want to convey as a last chapter to the time period that the music was made in. Hi everyone, I am super excited to let you know about my new band and new record with Grammy award, winning guitarist, and producer Eric Krasno.

We will release Krasno Moore Project: Book of Queens, digitally on March 17 via Concord Jazz. CD and Vinyl packages drop on October 6 and are available for pre-order now. 

Recorded at the magical Levon Helm Studios in Woodstock, New York and mixed by Jim Scott (Tedeschi Trucks Band, Wilco), Book of Queens is an instrumental organ trio tribute to women in music.

“When Stanton and I got together and decided to make a record we knew wanted to focus in on a concept that we both believed in. With the help of our wives (Lauren and Lauren) we started discussing a few ideas… We all agreed that a tribute to our favorite female singers and songwriters would be perfect. “ - Eric Krasno 

“With this record, we wanted to create an album that we would be proud to play for our wives. Something that we could play while making dinner or hanging on the beach. We wanted to put together a collection of songs that created an instant vibe from beginning to end that we would want to listen to and share with family and friends time and time again.” - Stanton Moore

Click link in my bio to Learn More about the Record and How to Get It!

Every song features Stanton Moore on Drums & Eric Finland on Organ/Keys. Special guests include Branford Marsalis, Cory Henry & Robert Randolph⚡️ We recorded it at the legendary Levon Helm Studios. Mixed by Jim Scott. Released by Concord Jazz. Very proud of this one… I hope you dig it and share with your friends 🙏🏽❤️⚡️ @stanton_moore @ericfinlandkeys @branfordmarsalis @coryhenry @robertrandolph @concordjazz

Check out our live performance for “Slow Burn” from our new album 'Krasno/Moore Project: Book Of Queens'.
 

“This song has such a relaxed, yet still grooving feel to it. I love how laid back the original is. I wanted to play this in our own way, so I tried a snare drum groove that hints at my New Orleans roots but still services the song. That's part of what's so great about playing organ trio versions of great songs, you can vary the song a bit to make it fit into the organ trio format, but then a great song still stands on its own as a strong tune.” - Stanton Moore

OUT NOW!! “Be Your Man” is available on all DSPs. Here’s the backstory on this one… @davegutter and I originally wrote this song for the @aaronneville album “Apache” back in 2016. Most of the songs from that album were taken from Aaron’s book of poems that we worked into songs. This one was just came from “man… imagine Aaron singing a song like this!”… and he killed it. Like many of the other tracks on the album, I sang the original demo. In most cases I just did what I thought Aaron would do…. Which as you can imagine was pretty hilarious (my voice does NOT and will not ever do what Aaron does) But this one felt good to sing. I later “covered” it live with my band a few times. But then i sent @otismcdonald the OG demo… he sent back a version that totally reimagined the groove and that was it.. i had to record it again. THANK YOU Otis, Aaron, Dave and my man @thenigelhall who added the insanely dope BGVs in the 2nd verse 🙏🏽✨❤️ I hope you all dig it and share it ⚡️
Check out the “Be Your Man” full lyric video on my @youtube page ✨Also streaming on all DSPs✨ Many more coming soon with my man @otismcdonald ⚡️ @davegutter @buythewax  @feelmusicgroup @ozgood ⚡️

“Unconditional Love” (acoustic version) is out now all streaming services. If you’ve seen me live in the past decade you’ve most likely heard this song. It was born in one of my 1st writing sessions with the great @davegutter ✨ His daughter @kani_gutter was young at the time and both he and I were going through relationship woes. He tried explain to me the concept of Unconditional Love and his relationship with Kani as this song came together and I nodded and went along because i did love the song but now this song means so much more to me being a dad. (Ok sappy part is over) Anyway, I’m glad i was able to record it again for this new acoustic project I’m creating. Attempting to play all the instruments myself and do it all in a room with just a microphone has been so much fun (check out slide for the shot of the tools used). I LOVE music technology but I’ve found myself drowning in options in the past few years. Limiting myself to a few instruments (check slide 3) has been super liberating and kind of meditative (avoiding screens can be good for the brain too!)😂. Thanks to @jamesthe8th for adding some BGVs & @low.lite for helping mix and record. I’ll be releasing a bunch of songs in this format over the next year, i hope you dig it.
